<br>
Instead of walking now and eating road dust Fox was swinging her legs back and forth off the back of one of a half dozen wagons.  The merchant was Tier Dal like Cinnistyr but the guards were all hired muscle out of the Freeport Militia.  The sidelong looks she'd earned being the only female in the party, and small had not gone unnoticed by her.  She would have to be cautious.<br>
<br>
Cinnistyr was snoring in the back of the wagon sleeping soundly on some expensive rugs tossed over sacks of spices and herbs or some such exotic commodity.  The wagon was one of the large enclosed types that required a team of four animals to pull.  Cinnistyr seemed to hold with the well known preference for sleeping days and being active nights of his race.<br>
<br>
Suddenly there was a cracking sound from one of the wagons ahead in the caravan and everyone slowed to a stop.  Fox could hear the curses of a teamster and several of the militia men came forward to lend a hand.  Fox craned her neck around the side of the wagon to see what had happened.<br>
<br>
The cart in front of her own had broken a piece of it's wooden wheel.  It would need replacing.  A tedious job that would require a lot of muscle and labor from the teamsters.  Fox hopped off the back of the wagon and walked around in the tall grass along the side of the rutted path they were traveling.<br>
<br>
The sun was slowly traveling down the sky towards the west and the shadows from the tall trees in this dim part of the forest seemed to stretch on a bit longer.  Cinnistyr's snores continued to rise and fall from the back of her own wagon.<br>
<br>
One of the militia road up next to her and gestured with an armored hand towards the surrounding forests.<br>
<br>
&quot;Best hope they get that their wheel fixed quick miss...this part o the road is the old part a Kithicor Forest....and I've heard plenty a stories that it's no good place ta be after the sun leaves the sky.&quot;<br>
<br>
He spat a foul black tar into the tall weeds along the road.  Some substance many of the militia seemed to chew on non stop.<br>
<br>
&quot;Whats wrong?  Bandits?&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;Nay, worse than that.&quot;  He leaned in closer and glanced around to make sure nobody else was listening.  &quot;It's they...undead...&quot;<br>
<br>
Fox raised a thin red eyebrow.  She'd seen undead before of course in the city.  In the slums following around the Tier Dal to be specific.  Freeport had laws against the use of necromancy but only in certain quarters of the town and the slums had no such restrictions.  Of course she'd never before encountered any roaming undead.  Nothing that was not under the strict control of sorcery.<br>
<br>
Fox drummed her fingertips on her rapier.  She went and retrieved her bow off of the wagon and climbed a nearby tree.  One without limbs close to the ground.  She watched as the teamsters and some of the militia grunted and groaned unloading the goods from the broken wagon so that it might be fixed.  If they meant to have the wagon repaired, reloaded and everyone underway before late in the afternoon it was going to be a close thing.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cinnistyr>Cinnistyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/21/02 8:33:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=645.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Job ( part two )</span><hr size=1>  So you want to know about Foxmane do you?<br>
<br>
She's the finest apprentice I have ever had, and learns her lessons quickly. <br>
<br>
She is deadly accurate with her dagger, and if she gets behind you, be prepared for a world of pain. <br>
<br>
I am very pleased with her training. <br>
I am very pleased I have had the chance to train her. <br>
<br>
Foxmane, I am very proud of you.<br>
